<td width="150" colspan="5" valign="middle" class="more_non_p">
The other principal mode of this tool is the graphical display of
an optical spectrum for a set of everyday and celestial objects
(the Sun, a sodium street lamp, a quasar, galaxies).
The students are encouraged to first view the spectrum as a histogram
of colors.  This is, of course, the proper discription
of the spectra that astronomers analyze for their research.
The student can also overlay the idealized spectrum to gain insight
into the relationship between color and wavelength.
